            "classSource": "Ishiir",
            "subclassShortName": "Song",
            "subclassSource": "Deoir",
            "level": 1,
            "header": 1,
            "entries": [
                "You gain {@variantrule Proficiency|Ishiir} in {@skill Performance}, if already {@variantrule Proficiency|Ishiir|proficient} your {@variantrule Proficiency|Ishiir} bonus is doubled. Additionally, you can use your Wisdom instead of your Charisma bonus for {@skill Performance} {@variantrule Ability Check|Ishiir|checks}."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Song of Strength",
            "source": "Deoir",
            "page": 1,
            "className": "Cleric",
            "classSource": "Ishiir",
            "subclassShortName": "Song",
            "subclassSource": "Deoir",
            "level": 1,
            "header": 1,
            "entries": [
                "You use your control over sound and song to create safety for your allies. As an {@variantrule Action|Ishiir} you can start singing, this does not inhibit you from casting spells with vocal components. For 1 minute when a creature within 30 feet of you makes an {@variantrule Attack Roll|Ishiir} you can use your {@variantrule Reaction|Ishiir} to impose {@variantrule Disadvantage|Ishiir} or {@variantrule Advantage|Ishiir} on that roll.",
                "At 10th level the {@variantrule Advantage|Ishiir} or {@variantrule Disadvantage|Ishiir} is for their entire attack action.",
                "You can use this feature a number of times equal to your {@variantrule Proficiency|Ishiir} bonus per {@variantrule Long Rest|Ishiir}."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Channel Divinity: Song of Protection",
            "source": "Deoir",
            "page": 1,
            "className": "Cleric",
            "classSource": "Ishiir",
            "subclassShortName": "Song",
            "subclassSource": "Deoir",
            "level": 2,
            "header": 2,
            "consumes": {
                "name": "Channel Divinity"
            },
            "entries": [
                "You can use your Channel Divinity to sing a song of protection. As an {@variantrule Action|Ishiir} choose a number of creatures equal to your {@variantrule Proficiency|Ishiir} bonus. These creatures gain an increase of 1 AC and add their {@variantrule Proficiency|Ishiir} when making {@condition Concentration|Ishiir} {@variantrule Ability Check|Ishiir|checks}. While singing this song you must use your {@variantrule Bonus Action|Ishiir} on subsequent turns to maintain the song, otherwise the song ends at the end of your turn."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Trained Ears",
            "source": "Deoir",
            "page": 1,
            "className": "Cleric",
            "classSource": "Ishiir",
            "subclassShortName": "Song",
            "subclassSource": "Deoir",
            "level": 6,
            "header": 2,
            "entries": [
                "Your mastery over sound grants you special abilities:",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "You have {@variantrule Resistance|Ishiir} to thunder damage.",
                        "When saving against an effect or a spell that is based on sound (DM discretion) or deals thunder damage, you gain {@variantrule Advantage|Ishiir} on the save."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Potent Spellcasting",
            "source": "Deoir",
            "page": 1,
            "className": "Cleric",
            "classSource": "Ishiir",
            "subclassShortName": "Song",
            "subclassSource": "Deoir",
            "level": 8,
            "header": 2,
            "entries": [
                "You add your Wisdom modifier to the damage you deal with any cleric cantrip and you can replace their damage type with thunder damage."
            ]
